##A mask from Japan

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Function description, every day a moving original true story.

The new crown pneumonia epidemic continues to spread, in the medical material shortage situation, the aid front, has become a life-and-death relay race. As the city was sealed off, Cindy, who was besieged in Wuhan, passed the baton of collecting donations to his friends in Japan.
This article is co-produced by true story and Universal Editorial (ID: new-lens) .

The new crown pneumonia epidemic continues to spread, in the medical material shortage situation, the aid front, has become a life-and-death relay race. As the city was sealed off, Cindy, who was besieged in Wuhan, passed the baton of collecting donations to his friends in Japan.

This article is co-produced by true story and Universal Editorial (ID: new-lens) .

Year: 2020

Location: Wuhan

"So short, so short! "

On January 22nd, after nine hours of waiting, Cindy finally heard back from his friend Kobayashi. Kobayashi, a nurse at a hospital in Wuhan, was on the front lines as the outbreak and panic spread, responding to Cindy's news that she was "not short of supplies" only in between high-intensity shifts.

Then Kobayashi sent over pictures of the hospital. After several nurses wore masks for a long time, deep indentation appeared on their faces. Because masks are scarce, they don't dare to take them off.

Cindy was once again aware of the extent of the material shortage. When Cindy returned to Wuhan from Hangzhou four days ago, he had no idea it would come to this: masks, disinfectant and Radix Isatidis had been snapped up; the number of confirmed cases was rising, and "when you open your eyes, it's all bad news" .

On Jan. 23, when news of the city's closure reached Cindy, who was suffocating and anxiously barging through her home, an idea popped into her head: She could raise money for masks for hospitals in dire need.

As president of Taobao's global buyers'alliance, Cindy plans to raise money for overseas medical supplies from her buyer friends in Japan. She will connect with logistics and support first-line medical staff.

After contacting the Wuhan first-line hospital to confirm the mask model, Cindy immediately set up a wechat group for "material donation" , spreading the news among friends. At this point, Wuhan mask is a hard to find. If only one person overseas responded, Cindy thought, then at least one of the medics could wear a mask.

More than Cindy expected, buyers poured into the crowd. Into the crowd, some of the Chinese buyers in Japan, but also she has cooperated with the head of the brand. As soon as they knew what was going on, they left the house and rushed to a nearby pharmacy. Photos of masks of different brands and sizes are popping up.

There is no rush to buy face masks in Japan at present. After the buyers took the photos, they immediately sent them to the group to confirm: "Can this be donated? "

Members of the Japan buyers union buy face masks

Looking at the various pictures, Cindy suddenly realized that he had been careless.

In the face of disease, time Minute to Win It. But the face masks in the picture, some do not meet the medical specifications, more importantly, the medical protective face masks in ordinary pharmacies is scarce, rare. Continuing to solicit donations in this way will not only take time and effort, but may even result in a lot of "futile" work.

Immediately, Cindy decided to change the way, fund raising, and then unified to the supplier payment, procurement. She announced the collection account in the group, you can donate in the group by order of the name and amount.

Cindy put his phone down after he announced that he was donating money to the charity. Getting people to call her directly was a test of trust, and she didn't know if she'd made it.

Cindy's thoughts were interrupted by frequent messages. Buyers have started to count off, and the number soon reached double digits. Relieved that the donation model was working, Cindy and his friends began sifting through Japan's supply lines.

By comparison, Cindy found that donations had exceeded 70,000 Renminbi, or about $1,000, after he locked up a medical website in Japan. Cindy was pleasantly surprised by a new choice.

Medical materials shortage, in a long period of time will be normal, demand exceeds supply, prices are bid up is an inevitable trend, and the current medical site more sources, moderate prices.

Gritting her teeth, Cindy and her friend said, "If you can't get the money together, give it yourself. " After discussing, they placed an order for 170,000 yuan, including medical masks and goggles.

Figure | partial list

Although the total amount of materials has exceeded 100,000 funds, but when the news spread, the next day, the number of people concerned about the donation continued to grow.

And with that, there are voices of doubt.

"Did you give your supplies to the Red Cross? " "How do you make sure the masks get to the paramedics? " "All the money went to buy masks? "

Even though time was short, Cindy insisted on answering the "100,000 Whys" of the netizens in words in the group. She decided that night to put the donation list, purchase orders published to let everyone see the progress of fund-raising.

In compiling the list, Cindy found that the account received more money than the total number of people in the group. In fact, there are many people quietly donated money, but did not leave their names.

When calculating the amount, Cindy also saw 5,000 to 10,000 Renminbi, or about $10,000, appearing many times. The donors who matched those numbers were almost all unfamiliar names to Cindy. Originally, "Japan buyers alliance" in many buyers shop owners, are actively pull around the people to help fund-raising.

To Cindy's surprise, the money came together the next day.

The next thing to solve is the logistics problem. In order to save transportation time, after consultation, the Japanese Logistics Company is prepared to provide free charter service. On January 30, the first batch of medical supplies flew directly from Osaka to Wuhan's Tianhe Airport. The Wuhan Union Hospital sent someone to the customs to sign for them and bring them back to the hospital.

Cargo from ÅŒsaka to Wuhan Tianhe Airport

When the paramedics sent him a signed message, Cindy felt the effort had not been in vain. With mixed feelings, she posted a friend's circle: "I hope everything will get better soon. "

On Jan. 27, Taobao's official Weibo account posted donations from Cindy and the Japan buyers alliance. "We are all together, " Gao Xiaosong tweeted and commented

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Screenshot by Gao Xiaosong

With the official Weibo confirmation and Gao Xiaosong's endorsement, the chorus of skepticism began to dwindle, and more people became aware of what Cindy and his friends were doing and joined in.

Cindy's Hospital, also from Wuhan radiation to Hubei and the country, a total of 13 hospitals including Wuhan Union Hospital, Jingzhou City Third People's Hospital, Hunan Nan County People's Hospital, including.

When Cindy made on demand purchases based on the conditions at each location, the problems she had been worried about were there. As the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic spread, Japan faced shortages of medical supplies, inadequate supplies and rising prices.

Goggles that cost around 200 yen have gone up 10 to 20 times. On several occasions, orders for advance deposits from Cindy were cancelled due to force majeure.

At the same time, supplies were being donated, and buyers in Japan were shuttling to pharmacies to collect face masks.

A buyer told Cindy that when he walked into the pharmacy, the clerk immediately told him to limit the purchase of the masks, but when the buyer explained that the masks were to be sent to Wuhan, China, the clerk immediately canceled the restriction and took out all the stock in the store, to help the buyer box, pack.

Japanese private organizations also donated, some boxes, in addition to writing "refueling Wuhan" , there are "mountains and rivers, exotic, same day. This makes Cindy, when she was in Japan, even "the same day, " or often Miss Wuhan Mountains and rivers and relatives, "No matter where people are, home is the only destination.

After graduating from college, Cindy made a decision to go to Japan, want to go abroad to exercise themselves.

As soon as she went out, Cindy learned the hard way that she could only do "menial jobs" at first, working up to four jobs a day: assembly-line food packing, restaurants, kitchens, factories because she didn't speak the language. And just like that, she slowly mastered Japanese. In 2007, Cindy became the first Chinese shopper to be hired at a well known store in Japan.

When Cindy became pregnant in 2011, she decided to quit her job and open a Taobao shop at home, switching to buying.

When she left her job, her Japanese colleagues wrote her dozens of cards filled with blessings: "hard work, often see you full of energy around. Hope to have an international baby, can speak any language. " "You quit your job and feel a lot of loneliness around you. After the baby is born, come and play with us again. ".

In May 2017, with six years of buyer experience and brand accumulation, Cindy established the "Japan buyer alliance" in Tokyo, Japan, to build a platform for buyers and brands. Her business covers beauty cosmetics, cosmetics, clothing, mother and baby, jewelry, health care products, and soon Taobao global purchase awarded the "Global Buyers Business Federation partners. ".

Since then, Cindy has spent more than 20 days a year traveling between Hangzhou and Japan, spending time with his parents and daughter in Wuhan.

On the eve of this year's Spring Festival, even though Wuhan had sounded the epidemic alert, Cindy decided to go home, "no matter what, we must be with our families in the New Year. ".

Now, every day, as he opened his eyes, Cindy began to connect with hospital staff about supplies, process donations and sift through Japanese supplies, comparing prices and arrival dates.

When Cindy saw that the supplies were up to standard and at the right price, he sent a screenshot to his hospital contacts to determine if they were available. If there were no problems, Cindy would buy them as soon as possible, and then sort out and sign the receipt after it arrived.

Supplies to medical staff

One night, buried in paperwork and receipts, Cindy was stunned by a transfer message. The transfer was small, only $300, but it put Cindy to shame.

The money came from Cindy's 9 year old daughter. Mother and daughter are rare to see once a month, the Spring Festival is two people get along with the time, but this time, she could not accompany her daughter, every day and buyers, hospital docking work.

Cindy did not expect her daughter to see, silent support, she wrote in the transfer message: "This is my money donation. " Found her daughter changed the face mask to "I love" , Cindy asked what it means, the daughter replied: "because the mother every day looking for masks, every day to buy a mask. " Cindy was moved, said gently to the daughter: "The mother will remember your love

At present, the "Japan Buyers Union" has raised 280,000 yuan in donations and a large number of materials. The latest batch of supplies, including masks, goggles, protective clothing, disinfectant and disposable gloves, will arrive at Wuhan Tianhe Airport on February 5.

As a native of Wuhan, Cindy retweeted a picture of "Go Wuhan! " On her friends' circle. The pixels in that image have become blurred with the number of retweets. But the words are still clear:

"close a city and protect a nation. Wuhan is an honorable city. Our city is sick, but we will cure it. I hope you will still like Wuhan when Haruhana is in full bloom and Cherry blossoms are in full bloom. "
